notes: HDX Signals monitors key datasets and generates automated emails when significant, negative changes are detected. Receive signals direct in your inbox by signing up on the [home page](https://eur02.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fdata.humdata.org%2Fsignals&data=05%7C02%7Cisabelle.tot%40un.org%7Cef19ac36eb2446def80508dc7a4cb394%7C0f9e35db544f4f60bdcc5ea416e6dc70%7C0%7C0%7C638519717049783120%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=ZvGD7L45DptYgKrWn2qOjs3HN5U6M2DwL9qjYKCI5Gs%3D&reserved=0). organization.description: The Humanitarian Data Exchange (HDX) is an open data sharing platform managed by the United Nations Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs. The HDX organization is managed by the HDX data team and is used to share data on behalf of a number of partners
